{
  "texts": [
    "The autocolor feature extraction method was utilised to reduce dimensionality while maintaining image accuracy.",
    "The results revealed that the models' accuracy, Mean Absolute Error (MAE), and Root Mean Square Error (RMSE) were compared (RMSE).",
    "Ensemble approaches such as Random Forest and Decision Stump obtained 95% accuracy for a 10-fold cross-validation strategy among the strategies used.",
    "The Bagging and Logit Boost algorithms were 95-97 percent accurate.",
    "Similarly, the J48 technique achieved the lowest error rate when compared to other classification models."
  ]
}